This paper focuses on machine learning approaches for part-of-speech tagging and named entity recognition for Greek, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the architecture model used for building the models, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the need for flexibility in out-of-vocabulary words, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on named entity recognition, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
